	<h2>About Me</h2>
	<p>Hi my name is Manuel Huerta a.k.a. Manny, I'm a student at Wyncode Academy and computer development is my passion. I was born in Caracas, Venezuela but was raised in South Florida since the age of five. I have loved technology all my life. Since my first Nintendo to my first computer, tech is my first love and something that I want to make my career. My previous work experience includes retail at Gamestop and I also have a lot of experience in education. My first teaching job was as a subsitute teacher at Renaissance Charter School. After that i got a position at Nova Southeastern University in their preschool. At Baudhuin Preschool we did reseach and development for children living with autism.</p>

	<p>I am currently at Wyncode Academy learning the art of computer languages; they include Ruby laguage, Rails, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS. Being in Wyncode has taught me more then I ever knew about computers and how they work. When I finish my cohort at Wyncode I want to get a job in the web developer industry.</p>

